headlines.description: Bryce Love proved he could fill in quite nicely as Christian McCaffrey's replacement at Stanford, scoring a touchdown and rushing for 180 yards to lead the No.14 Cardinal to a 62-7 victory over Rice on Sunday in the Sydney College Football Cup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Christian who? Love stars in No. 14 Stanford's win over Rice

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Stanford dominates Rice in 55-point win) 2017/08/27 ESHEET

events.name: South Florida Bulls at San Jose State Spartans

headlines.description: Quinton Flowers threw two TD passes and D'Ernest Johnson had two TD runs in a dominant second quarter that helped No. 19 South Florida overcome an early 16-point hole to beat San Jose State 42-22 on Saturday in the first game under coach Charlie Strong.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 19 S. Florida beats San Jose St. 42-22 after slow start

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (South Florida rolls past SJSU) 2017/08/27 ESHEET

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Colorado State Rams

headlines.description: Linebacker Tre Thomas scored on a 44-yard interception return to lead a Colorado State defense that forced five turnovers, Nick Stevens threw three TD passes and the Rams opened their new on-campus stadium with a 58-27 win over Oregon State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado St. opens new stadium by beating Oregon St 58-27

events.name: Portland State Vikings at BYU Cougars

headlines.description: Tanner Mangum completed 16 of 27 passes for 194 yards and a touchdown, and Squally Canada had 13 carries for a career-high 90 yards and a score to help BYU beat Portland State 20-6 Saturday in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mangum, Canada lead BYU to 20-6 win over Portland State

video.headline: Mangum leads BYU to the win

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF highlight (Mangum leads BYU to the win) 2017/08/26 ESHEET

events.name: Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: Dru Brown threw a 7-yard touchdown pass to Metuisela 'Unga with 48 seconds left to lift Hawaii to a 38-35 win over Massachusetts in the season opener for both teams Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown's last minute TD pass lifts Hawaii over UMass 38-35
